## Coding Standards

### TypeScript
- `strict: true` — no `any` types, no `@ts-ignore`
- Named exports for components (no default exports)
- Path aliases: `@/components`, `@/lib`, `@/hooks`, `@/types`
- Zod for runtime validation at API boundaries

### Styling
- Tailwind CSS only — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- All brand colors via CSS variables (defined in `globals.css`)
- All brand tokens in `tailwind.config.ts`
- Never hardcode hex values in component files

### Components
- One component per file
- Server Components by default, `"use client"` only when needed
- Every page route has `loading.tsx` and `error.tsx`
- Semantic HTML (main, nav, section, article)

## Design System

This project uses the **{ARCHETYPE}** aesthetic direction.

**Differentiation decision:** {DIFFERENTIATION}

**Token references:** See `globals.css` for CSS variables, `tailwind.config.ts` for Tailwind mappings.

When adding new pages or components:
1. Use existing tokens — don't introduce new colors or fonts
2. Follow the established layout patterns from existing pages
3. Ensure the differentiation decision is present in new components where applicable
4. Run the anti-slop checklist before finalizing (see design-direction.md)

